Venus (planet)

gold/chemical element Au/generic term for lustrous and ductile metals/money/golden/highly respected/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]

sentences.english: The earth was as completely cloud-shrouded as normally is the planet Venus.
sentences.chinese: 整个地球就像金星平时那样完全被云雾掩盖着。

sentences.english: The sign is ruled by Venus.
sentences.chinese: 天秤座的守护星是金星。

sentences.english: In this 8th house will be Jupiter: a planet that often represents joy.
sentences.chinese: 而第八宫的主星是金星，通常代表着喜悦。

sentences.english: With an excess of carbon dioxide, Venus is hot enough to melt lead.
sentences.chinese: 而二氧化碳过多的话，金星可以热到能融化铅的地步。

sentences.english: Lewis. A Mars rampant with life. A water-covered Venus populated with floating, living islands.
sentences.chinese: 水覆盖下的金星移居来一些漂泊的栖身用的“岛屿”。

sentences.english: The Sun will be moving through this house too, as will Venus most of the month.
sentences.chinese: 太阳也会经过这一个宫，这个月金星是最的。

sentences.english: The South Korean Foreign Minister Kim Sung-hwan also said that he suspected that there were additional nuclear facilities in North Korea.
sentences.chinese: 韩国外交部长金星焕也怀疑朝鲜还有另外的核设施。

sentences.english: This is a star-spangled day, deserving of a gold star on your calendar.
sentences.chinese: 这是个星光灿烂的子，值得在历上画一个大金星。

sentences.english: Venus rarely goes out of phase, but fortunately, this will only be retrograde for six weeks.
sentences.chinese: 金星很少异相，不过幸运的是，这次逆行只有六周。

sentences.english: Bosworth also held a separate meeting with South Korean Foreign Minister Kim Sung-hwan.
sentences.chinese: 博斯沃思还和韩国外交通商部长官金星焕举行了会谈。

sentences.english: Visible on the upper right are the crescent Moon and the bright planet Venus.
sentences.chinese: 右上角可见弦月与一旁明亮的金星。

sentences.english: Venus will turn Retrograde in Scorpio, putting a strong focus on sexuality and intimate relationships.
sentences.chinese: 金星会在天蝎座逆行转，强烈关注性和亲密关系。

sentences.english: Imagine that men are from  Mars and women are from  Venus.
sentences.chinese: 请想像男人来自火星，女人来自金星的景象。

sentences.english: A reclassification of the family Thelypteridaceae from the mainland of Asia.
sentences.chinese: 亚洲大陆的金星蕨科的新分类系统。

sentences.english: A water-covered Venus populated with floating, living "islands."
sentences.chinese: 水覆盖下的金星移居来一些漂浮的居住用的“岛屿”。

sentences.english: The first week of March will be special, thanks to Venus.
sentences.chinese: 拜金星所赐，3月的第一周真是非凡。
